# ❌ Critical Debug Ledger (Common Mistakes)

[x] Mistake: `if(existingUser.email === email)` ➔ **CRASHES** server with 500 status when user registration is completely fresh (null entity object).
[√] Fix: Check pointer safety pattern first ➔ `if(existingUser && existingUser.email === email)`

[x] Mistake: Invalid switch string typo checks (`send-wellcome-mail` vs `send-wellcome-email`). Worker ends lifecycle silently.
[√] Fix: Remove raw strings. Use `EMAIL_JOBS.SEND_WELCOME` constant maps. If registry mismatch happens, trigger absolute crash line ➔ `if (!handler) throw new Error("Critical crash: Mismatch event routing execution.");`




