# 📁 The Ultimate Domain-Driven Folder Map

Notes:
* This exact structural hierarchy completely isolates features.
* The main app knows absolutely nothing about inner domain files except what is leaked via `index.ts`.

```text
src/
├── config/
│   └── redis.ts                     ➔ Shared Redis connector instance pool
├── modules/
│   └── email/                       ➔ 🔥 COMPLETE SELF-CONTAINED KINGDOM
│       ├── constants/
│       │   └── job.constant.ts      ➔ Strict type-safe job names map (No Typos)
│       ├── templates/
│       │   └── email.template.ts    ➔ Pure presentation HTML code strings
│       ├── services/
│       │   └── nodemailer.service.ts➔ Raw transport network dispatcher layer
│       ├── queue/
│       │   ├── email.queue.ts       ➔ BullMQ instance holding production backoffs
│       │   └── email.events.ts      ➔ Telemetry tracking listeners (Delayed, Active)
│       ├── handlers/
│       │   ├── base.handler.ts      ➔ Strict contract abstract interface structure
│       │   └── welcome.handler.ts   ➔ Core transactional email business logic
│       ├── worker/
│       │   └── email.worker.ts      ➔ 20-Line Traffic Police dispatch engine
│       ├── producer/
│       │   └── email.producer.ts    ➔ Abstracted client interactions bridge
│       └── index.ts                 ➔ Module Facade Gatekeeper (Strict Boundaries)
└── index.ts                         ➔ Core App Bootstrapper & Graceful Shutdown traps
```

