# ⏱️ Precision Live Telemetry Event Tracking

Notes:
* Tracks delays, processing states, and errors in real-time.
* Crucial for debugging asynchronous race-conditions on high-traffic pipelines.

[js] Telemetry Monitoring Engine:
File Location: `src/modules/email/queue/email.events.ts`
```typescript
import { QueueEvents } from "bullmq";
import { redisConnectionConfig } from "../../../config/redis.js";

export const emailEvents = new QueueEvents("email-core-queue", {
  connection: redisConnectionConfig,
});

// ⏳ Telemetry Stage 1: Triggered when a job is waiting on a delay countdown loop
emailEvents.on("delayed", ({ jobId, delay }) => {
  console.log(`\n==================================================`);
  console.log(`⏳ [TELEMETRY] Job STATE: DELAYED | ID: ${jobId}`);
  console.log(`⏱️  Timer: ${delay / 1000} seconds remaining before execution loop...`);
  console.log(`==================================================`);
});

// 🏃‍♂️ Telemetry Stage 2: Triggered when countdown ends and Worker locks the task slot
emailEvents.on("active", ({ jobId }) => {
  console.log(`🚀 [TELEMETRY] Job STATE: ACTIVE | ID: ${jobId} (Worker pipeline lock initialized)`);
});

// ✅ Telemetry Stage 3: Triggered when Nodemailer delivers payload with no network exceptions
emailEvents.on("completed", ({ jobId }) => {
  console.log(`✅ [TELEMETRY] Job STATE: COMPLETED | ID: ${jobId} (State flushed cleanly from pool)\n`);
});

// ❌ Telemetry Stage 4: Triggered when retries finish or catastrophic failure occurs
emailEvents.on("failed", ({ jobId, failedReason }) => {
  console.error(`❌ [TELEMETRY] Job STATE: FAILED | ID: ${jobId}`);
  console.error(`🚨 Root Stack Reason: ${failedReason}\n`);
});
```

