# 🏭 Complete Integration: How to use the Module inside Auth flow

Notes: Look how incredibly fresh the rest of your app stays! No BullMQ imports anywhere else.

[js] Example Auth Controller Dispatch:
File Location: `src/modules/auth/auth.controller.ts`
```typescript
import { emailProducer } from "../email/index.js"; // Strictly importing from public gateway edge

export const signup = async (req, res) => {
  // 1. ... [Validations pass successfully] ...
  // 2. ... [User created safely inside database layer] ...
  
  // 3. Fire and Forget using type-safe abstracted wrapper interface
  await emailProducer.queueWelcomeEmail({
    email: "bhai@example.com",
    name: "ARG Developer Partner"
  });

  // 4. Return response instantly without locking the network thread pool
  return res.status(201).json({ success: true, message: "Account generated successfully!" });
};
```

